WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

2
00:00:00.450 --> 00:00:01.930
Defend the castle!

3
00:01:11.730 --> 00:01:13.930
Hasn't the crown prince escaped yet?

4
00:01:13.930 --> 00:01:17.050
It's not that simple! The princes 
are too young to flee swiftly!

5
00:01:20.820 --> 00:01:22.560
In any case, we defend 
this place to the death!

6
00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:24.390
Hold until the signal bell rings!

7
00:01:42.640 --> 00:01:45.760
<i>Here is the man who brought about this war,</i>

8
00:01:47.650 --> 00:01:49.820
<i>the emperor of Galkhein:</i>

9
00:01:50.290 --> 00:01:52.040
<i>Arnold Hein.</i>

10
00:02:06.390 --> 00:02:07.280
Here we go!

11
00:02:07.280 --> 00:02:08.290
Sir!

12
00:03:37.400 --> 00:03:40.700
<i>I lived this life to the fullest, too.</i>

13
00:03:45.070 --> 00:03:46.320
<i>But...</i>

14
00:03:47.290 --> 00:03:51.000
<i>Next time... Next time, I'll...</i>

15
00:04:16.030 --> 00:04:18.500
Rishe Irmgard Weitzner!

16
00:04:18.500 --> 00:04:22.390
You are a devious woman unworthy of 
being the fiancée of a crown prince!

17
00:04:22.390 --> 00:04:26.710
Today, as of this moment, 
I annul my engagement to you!

18
00:04:28.800 --> 00:04:30.660
Very well. I understand.

19
00:04:30.660 --> 00:04:31.720
Huh?

20
00:04:31.720 --> 00:04:33.780
Hold on. I'm voiding our engagement.

21
00:04:33.780 --> 00:04:36.670
You must be worried about 
what will happen to you now.

22
00:04:36.670 --> 00:04:38.140
No, not in the least.

23
00:04:38.420 --> 00:04:39.570
What?

24
00:04:40.780 --> 00:04:42.080
If you'll pardon me.

25
00:04:42.080 --> 00:04:43.730
Huh? W-Wait!

26
00:04:43.730 --> 00:04:45.680
Rishe? Where are you going?

27
00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:47.390
Listen to me!

28
00:04:46.340 --> 00:04:48.440
<i>Once again, I've returned.</i>

29
00:04:47.390 --> 00:04:51.150
I spent a whole week thinking about 
how I'd read off your list of crimes!

30
00:04:51.150 --> 00:04:54.420
Listen! Hey! You! Come back here!

31
00:04:53.290 --> 00:04:56.190
<i>I already know how I'm to be treated.</i>

32
00:04:54.420 --> 00:04:58.310
Halt! Rishe! Listen to me 
when I'm speaking to you!

33
00:04:57.350 --> 00:04:58.530
<i>After all,</i>

34
00:04:59.820 --> 00:05:03.470
<i>this is the seventh time I've relived my life.</i>

35
00:05:12.690 --> 00:05:15.350
<i>Even now, I can recall it clearly...</i>

36
00:05:15.350 --> 00:05:17.660
<i>My very first life.</i>

37
00:05:18.150 --> 00:05:20.750
Rishe Irmgard Weitzner!

38
00:05:20.750 --> 00:05:24.480
You are a devious woman unworthy of 
being the fiancée of a crown prince!

39
00:05:24.480 --> 00:05:28.640
Today, as of this moment, 
I annul my engagement to you!

40
00:05:28.640 --> 00:05:31.640
Wh-What? You're breaking off our engagement?

41
00:05:31.640 --> 00:05:33.760
But... why?

42
00:05:33.760 --> 00:05:36.140
You will be exiled from this kingdom.

43
00:05:36.490 --> 00:05:38.310
Crown Prince Dietrich...

44
00:05:38.310 --> 00:05:40.400
Do you really mean what you're saying?

45
00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:43.350
I will now list your crimes.

46
00:05:43.350 --> 00:05:44.770
Crimes?!

47
00:05:46.290 --> 00:05:49.910
We are a ducal house, with an 
oath of loyalty to the crown.

48
00:05:49.910 --> 00:05:53.040
To think that you, my only daughter, 
would betray that oath.

49
00:05:53.040 --> 00:05:55.540
You should be ashamed, Rishe.

50
00:05:55.540 --> 00:05:58.420
They're false accusations! 
Please, listen to me!

51
00:05:58.420 --> 00:06:00.930
Father! Mother!

52
00:06:03.260 --> 00:06:05.130
<i>My engagement was broken.</i>

53
00:06:05.130 --> 00:06:06.940
<i>My family abandoned me.</i>

54
00:06:07.420 --> 00:06:10.690
<i>With nothing but the clothes on 
my back, I wandered aimlessly.</i>

55
00:06:21.790 --> 00:06:24.150
<i>What do I do now?</i>

56
00:06:28.050 --> 00:06:30.470
Is it fun staring at the ground like that,

57
00:06:30.470 --> 00:06:31.700
young lady?

58
00:06:32.530 --> 00:06:34.200
<i>That's when it happened.</i>

59
00:06:34.200 --> 00:06:37.090
<i>That's when I met that band 
of traveling merchants.</i>

60
00:06:38.320 --> 00:06:40.860
You look like you're going 
through a rough patch.

61
00:06:40.860 --> 00:06:43.710
This cart is headed to the next 
country over. Want a ride?

62
00:06:43.710 --> 00:06:45.530
You sure about this, chief?

63
00:06:45.530 --> 00:06:48.620
You're a real pushover when it 
comes to beauties like her.

64
00:06:49.540 --> 00:06:52.190
<i>Are these people merchants?</i>

65
00:06:50.270 --> 00:06:52.190
That's true!

66
00:06:52.770 --> 00:06:56.350
Idiots. I've got a better eye 
for people than you think.

67
00:06:59.050 --> 00:07:03.050
Even in the moonlight, that silk 
shines with an impressive luster.

68
00:07:03.730 --> 00:07:05.480
It's Vishkulha made, isn't it?

69
00:07:06.900 --> 00:07:11.230
So you're from the royal family, 
or maybe a duke's house.

70
00:07:11.230 --> 00:07:13.260
A noble young lady like you 
out this late can only—

71
00:07:13.260 --> 00:07:14.370
Excuse me!

72
00:07:15.520 --> 00:07:18.450
Would you buy this ring from me?

73
00:07:26.520 --> 00:07:29.590
We don't just buy and sell things.

74
00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:34.260
We find goods that set our 
hearts ablaze—that fire us up—

75
00:07:34.260 --> 00:07:37.260
and we sell them to people who are 
just as excited about them as us.

76
00:07:37.260 --> 00:07:42.540
Both buyer and seller love the wares, and 
that's what creates the profit in the trade.

77
00:07:43.580 --> 00:07:47.020
That's our creed—the creed 
of the Aria Trading Company.

78
00:07:49.400 --> 00:07:52.550
That face... You just thought, 
"that sounds like fun," didn't you?

79
00:07:52.550 --> 00:07:54.190
I-I...

80
00:07:54.190 --> 00:07:57.790
Your life's a blank slate right now, isn't it?

81
00:07:58.540 --> 00:08:02.080
Why don't you take this opportunity 
to embark on the path of a merchant?

82
00:08:02.370 --> 00:08:06.540
Me? I've never even considered it.

83
00:08:06.540 --> 00:08:10.970
You've been freed from your stifling destiny 
as the wife of a crown prince.

84
00:08:11.450 --> 00:08:14.390
You can go anywhere.

85
00:08:14.860 --> 00:08:16.550
You're free to do whatever you want.

86
00:08:20.170 --> 00:08:23.220
Free... to do what I want...

87
00:08:24.700 --> 00:08:26.960
You have a good eye.

88
00:08:26.960 --> 00:08:28.070
And...

89
00:08:28.390 --> 00:08:34.070
You possess the kind of amazing luck that 
led you to a friendly caravan like ours!

90
00:08:34.070 --> 00:08:38.080
If you became a merchant, I think 
things would get pretty interesting.

91
00:08:41.180 --> 00:08:42.600
How about it? Are you in?

92
00:08:42.600 --> 00:08:46.080
Yes, please! Please teach me 
how to be a merchant!

93
00:08:47.480 --> 00:08:49.170
<i>My first life.</i>

94
00:08:49.720 --> 00:08:53.100
<i>I learned how to trade under Chief Tully.</i>

95
00:08:53.620 --> 00:08:56.690
<i>Then I set out on my own as a merchant.</i>

96
00:08:56.690 --> 00:09:01.370
<i>I traveled the world, pursuing my newfound 
dream of visiting every country in it.</i>

97
00:09:02.110 --> 00:09:04.820
<i>And then, with just one 
country left on my list,</i>

98
00:09:04.820 --> 00:09:07.450
<i>I was swept up in a war...</i>

99
00:09:07.840 --> 00:09:10.500
<i>and ended up losing my life.</i>

100
00:09:32.410 --> 00:09:33.510
What?

101
00:09:32.610 --> 00:09:35.200
Rishe Irmgard Weitzner!

102
00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:38.960
You are a devious woman unworthy of 
being the fiancée of a crown prince!

103
00:09:38.960 --> 00:09:43.060
Today, as of this moment, 
I annul my engagement to you!

104
00:09:43.310 --> 00:09:46.000
Crown Prince Dietrich?

105
00:09:47.990 --> 00:09:49.610
<i>What is all this?</i>

106
00:09:50.450 --> 00:09:53.220
<i>My dress and ring are just 
as they were on that day.</i>

107
00:09:53.890 --> 00:09:56.570
<i>Is this... a dream?</i>

108
00:09:56.690 --> 00:09:59.820
You will be exiled from this kingdom.

109
00:10:02.560 --> 00:10:03.830
It hurts.

110
00:10:04.750 --> 00:10:07.580
Does the dissolution of our engagement 
sadden you that much?

111
00:10:07.580 --> 00:10:08.970
<i>If this isn't a dream...</i>

112
00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:09.680
I see. I see.

113
00:10:08.970 --> 00:10:10.830
<i>then I don't have a moment to lose!</i>

114
00:10:10.830 --> 00:10:13.590
<i>Soon, they'll lock me out of the mansion!</i>

115
00:10:14.140 --> 00:10:15.290
If you'll pardon me.

116
00:10:15.290 --> 00:10:16.840
Huh? W-Wait!

117
00:10:16.840 --> 00:10:18.470
Rishe? Where are you going?

118
00:10:18.470 --> 00:10:19.710
Listen to me!

119
00:10:18.970 --> 00:10:21.200
<i>Thank you, gods!</i>

120
00:10:19.710 --> 00:10:23.500
I spent a whole week thinking about 
how I'd read off your list of crimes!

121
00:10:21.200 --> 00:10:24.950
<i>I don't understand how, 
but I've been given a second chance at life!</i>

122
00:10:23.500 --> 00:10:25.600
Listen! Hey! You! Come back here!

123
00:10:25.600 --> 00:10:28.140
<i>The only regret I harbored about that night...</i>

124
00:10:28.140 --> 00:10:31.110
<i>was that I wasn't able to bring 
more of my personal effects with me.</i>

125
00:10:31.110 --> 00:10:33.070
<i>If I'd had more seed money as a merchant,</i>

126
00:10:33.070 --> 00:10:35.560
<i>I would have been able to grow 
my enterprise more quickly.</i>

127
00:10:36.590 --> 00:10:40.950
<i>Now I just need to meet Chief Tully and 
everyone from the Aria Trading Company again!</i>

128
00:10:42.480 --> 00:10:47.250
<i>But by the time I arrived, the Company's 
carts had already passed through.</i>

129
00:10:47.830 --> 00:10:52.000
<i>It can't be. Is this because I went 
back home and gathered my things?</i>

130
00:10:58.210 --> 00:11:01.990
The <i>Pictorial Herbal of Foreign Medicinal 
Plants</i> my grandmother left me...

131
00:11:03.010 --> 00:11:05.630
<i>Unlike last time, I have money.</i>

132
00:11:05.630 --> 00:11:08.530
<i>In which case, I just need to 
decide what to do with it.</i>

133
00:11:10.290 --> 00:11:14.590
<i>In my second life, I sold my possessions, 
used the proceeds to cross the sea,</i>

134
00:11:14.590 --> 00:11:16.800
<i>and chose to study medicine.</i>

135
00:11:17.560 --> 00:11:20.350
<i>With information on where 
medicinal plants grew,</i>

136
00:11:20.350 --> 00:11:22.700
<i>and the knowledge of when 
epidemics would spread,</i>

137
00:11:22.700 --> 00:11:27.200
<i>I was able to put the experience 
I'd gained from my first life to good use.</i>

138
00:11:28.270 --> 00:11:30.750
<i>One day, I traveled to a kingdom in the north</i>

139
00:11:30.750 --> 00:11:33.410
<i>and saved a sickly prince.</i>

140
00:11:34.040 --> 00:11:37.000
Your complexion is looking much better, Kyle.

141
00:11:37.470 --> 00:11:39.300
Thank you, Weitzner.

142
00:11:39.300 --> 00:11:42.510
I feel so well today that 
I even surprise myself.

143
00:11:42.510 --> 00:11:44.510
It's all thanks to your medicine.

144
00:11:44.710 --> 00:11:46.260
I'm so glad.

145
00:11:46.260 --> 00:11:50.790
<i>My life as an herbalist was fulfilling 
and incredibly rewarding.</i>

146
00:11:51.320 --> 00:11:55.020
<i>But once again in my second life, 
just as I'd been in my first...</i>

147
00:11:55.020 --> 00:11:58.350
<i>I was swept up in a war and died.</i>

148
00:12:07.690 --> 00:12:10.290
Rishe Irmgard Weitzner!

149
00:12:10.290 --> 00:12:14.130
You are a devious woman unworthy of 
being the fiancée of a crown prince!

150
00:12:14.130 --> 00:12:17.590
Today, as of this moment, 
I annul my engagement to—

151
00:12:17.590 --> 00:12:18.840
I understand and comply.

152
00:12:18.840 --> 00:12:20.240
Understand what?!

153
00:12:20.990 --> 00:12:23.800
<i>For my third life, I set my 
sights on something else:</i>

154
00:12:23.800 --> 00:12:28.040
<i>a specialized branch of study that 
I'd learned of in my previous life,</i>

155
00:12:28.830 --> 00:12:31.750
<i>and a genius scholar who specialized in it.</i>

156
00:12:32.310 --> 00:12:36.880
<i>For me, his was the familiar face of 
an acquaintance from my second life,</i>

157
00:12:36.880 --> 00:12:38.760
<i>Doctor Michel Evan.</i>

158
00:12:39.910 --> 00:12:42.440
No matter how perfect you 
believe your theory to be,

159
00:12:42.440 --> 00:12:47.360
it is only through repeated experimentation 
that you may draw a valid conclusion.

160
00:12:47.360 --> 00:12:48.830
Yes, Doctor!

161
00:12:48.830 --> 00:12:52.150
You really do seem to enjoy your research.

162
00:12:52.150 --> 00:12:55.330
Learning new things is so very exciting!

163
00:12:55.330 --> 00:12:57.170
It expands my horizons,

164
00:12:57.170 --> 00:13:00.210
and causes me to view even yesterday's 
sights in a whole new light!

165
00:13:01.950 --> 00:13:04.080
<i>After that, the good doctor and I parted ways,</i>

166
00:13:04.080 --> 00:13:08.100
<i>and as I continued my research alone, 
once again...</i>

167
00:13:08.470 --> 00:13:11.390
<i>I was swept up in a war and died.</i>

168
00:13:12.870 --> 00:13:16.980
<i>From serving as a handmaid in a 
duke's household in my fourth life,</i>

169
00:13:16.980 --> 00:13:20.410
<i>to disguising myself as a man 
and fighting as a knight in my sixth life...</i>

170
00:13:20.990 --> 00:13:23.540
<i>In each life, I found a sense of fulfillment,</i>

171
00:13:23.540 --> 00:13:25.210
<i>and I enjoyed them all very much.</i>

172
00:13:25.870 --> 00:13:26.810
<i>But...</i>

173
00:13:29.430 --> 00:13:32.050
<i>In each new life of mine, 
once five years have passed,</i>

174
00:13:32.050 --> 00:13:34.380
<i>I die without fail.</i>

175
00:13:35.250 --> 00:13:38.330
<i>Even when I didn't die from 
being swept up in the war,</i>

176
00:13:38.330 --> 00:13:41.180
<i>I spent my days so busy 
I nearly died from overwork!</i>

177
00:13:41.630 --> 00:13:44.340
<i>And now, I find myself reliving 
my life for the seventh time.</i>

178
00:13:44.650 --> 00:13:48.340
<i>I want to spend this go-around taking it easy.</i>

179
00:13:48.340 --> 00:13:50.130
<i>And more than anything else,</i>

180
00:13:50.910 --> 00:13:53.750
<i>I swear I'll live a long life this time!</i>

181
00:13:54.820 --> 00:13:56.270
<i>Now that I think about it,</i>

182
00:13:56.270 --> 00:13:58.900
<i>up until this point, I've always 
left through the main entrance.</i>

183
00:14:01.550 --> 00:14:05.070
<i>But as I am now, this way will be quicker—</i>

184
00:14:09.760 --> 00:14:13.190
I'm so very... sorry...

185
00:14:21.680 --> 00:14:23.550
You certainly charged around that corner—

186
00:14:26.460 --> 00:14:28.570
Emperor Arnold Hein!

187
00:14:28.990 --> 00:14:30.590
You know who I am?

188
00:14:31.050 --> 00:14:33.680
This is the first time 
I've come to this kingdom.

189
00:14:36.040 --> 00:14:40.170
My name is Rishe Imgard Weitzner.

190
00:14:40.930 --> 00:14:43.330
Though this is the first time we have met,

191
00:14:43.330 --> 00:14:45.690
I must say that your reputation precedes you.

192
00:14:45.690 --> 00:14:48.950
Just now, you called me 
"emperor," didn't you?

193
00:14:50.560 --> 00:14:55.410
As my father, the emperor, still lives, 
I am no more than a crown prince. And yet...

194
00:14:55.410 --> 00:14:57.690
Well...

195
00:15:00.390 --> 00:15:03.240
My deepest apologies, Your Royal Highness.

196
00:15:03.650 --> 00:15:08.050
In my flustered state, it seems 
I misspoke most disrespectfully.

197
00:15:08.510 --> 00:15:12.280
However, my engagement has presently 
been annulled, so I am in no small hurry.

198
00:15:12.280 --> 00:15:14.020
I must take my leave now.

199
00:15:16.610 --> 00:15:18.020
A broken engagement?

200
00:15:32.070 --> 00:15:33.150
Wait.

201
00:16:01.420 --> 00:16:02.470
There.

202
00:16:12.420 --> 00:16:14.200
Has something happened?

203
00:16:14.360 --> 00:16:16.900
Oliver, ready my horse.

204
00:16:16.900 --> 00:16:18.420
As you command.

205
00:16:18.420 --> 00:16:20.200
What are you planning to do?

206
00:16:33.720 --> 00:16:36.850
This body has far too little endurance.

207
00:16:36.850 --> 00:16:39.060
I'll have to train all over again.

208
00:16:40.840 --> 00:16:41.770
What?

209
00:16:44.480 --> 00:16:46.730
I've spent a week planning it—my masterpiece!

210
00:16:47.040 --> 00:16:49.270
Prince Dietrich! It's Lady Rishe!

211
00:16:49.270 --> 00:16:50.230
What?

212
00:16:50.230 --> 00:16:52.990
Out of the way! You, let me pass!

213
00:16:53.210 --> 00:16:54.890
You took your time, Rishe.

214
00:16:54.890 --> 00:16:56.990
You don't wish to hear your beloved,

215
00:16:56.990 --> 00:17:00.250
me, speak more words of 
condemnation. I understand.

216
00:17:00.250 --> 00:17:02.400
However, it won't go as you wish.

217
00:17:02.400 --> 00:17:05.340
Bringing the hammer of justice down 
upon wicked women such as you

218
00:17:05.340 --> 00:17:08.250
is one of my duties as the 
future king of this land!

219
00:17:06.450 --> 00:17:08.250
Not only did I fail to make it in time,

220
00:17:08.250 --> 00:17:11.510
this is the absolute worst 
timing of any of my lives.

221
00:17:11.510 --> 00:17:13.780
If only I'd arrived later 
than in my first life,

222
00:17:13.780 --> 00:17:16.430
I might have avoided seeing his face again.

223
00:17:14.510 --> 00:17:16.430
What are you mumbling about?

224
00:17:17.330 --> 00:17:18.540
It's just as I thought.

225
00:17:19.260 --> 00:17:21.770
At the soirée, you reacted 
indifferently to my proclamation,

226
00:17:21.770 --> 00:17:24.570
but it seems to me that you 
are deeply saddened at heart.

227
00:17:24.570 --> 00:17:25.270
Pardon?

228
00:17:25.270 --> 00:17:29.790
My annulment of the engagement has you in 
such despair that you don't know what to do.

229
00:17:29.790 --> 00:17:32.530
You've been walking, wandering, heartbroken.

230
00:17:32.530 --> 00:17:35.150
I can tell that much with a single glance!

231
00:17:35.150 --> 00:17:38.660
Your dress is covered in mud, 
and you have wounds all over your body.

232
00:17:38.660 --> 00:17:41.790
To think that the grief of an engagement 
broken reduced you to such a state—

233
00:17:41.790 --> 00:17:43.290
Are you stupid?

234
00:17:43.290 --> 00:17:44.070
What?

235
00:17:44.070 --> 00:17:46.370
Grief does not dirty a dress.

236
00:17:46.370 --> 00:17:50.710
More importantly, I am not sad that 
you have broken our engagement.

237
00:17:50.710 --> 00:17:52.250
Wh-What?!

238
00:17:52.630 --> 00:17:56.130
Has the crown prince been 
spurned by Lady Rishe?

239
00:17:56.130 --> 00:18:00.200
But Lady Rishe wasn't the one 
who broke the engagement, was she?

240
00:18:00.200 --> 00:18:04.280
Still, the crown prince looks 
more hurt than she does to me.

241
00:18:05.040 --> 00:18:06.390
You're right!

242
00:18:06.390 --> 00:18:08.350
You there! You're being disrespectful!

243
00:18:08.350 --> 00:18:09.400
The nerve of you peasants!

244
00:18:09.400 --> 00:18:14.350
<i>I am truly glad I did not have to spend 
any of my lives married to this person.</i>

245
00:18:15.050 --> 00:18:19.640
Your Royal Highness, you are meant 
to protect and cherish your people.

246
00:18:19.640 --> 00:18:21.960
You mustn't speak like you just did.

247
00:18:21.960 --> 00:18:24.310
You are the one who needs 
to correct their demeanor.

248
00:18:24.310 --> 00:18:26.800
Don't you have any intention 
of asking for my forgiveness?

249
00:18:26.800 --> 00:18:28.180
No. Not the slightest.

250
00:18:28.180 --> 00:18:31.660
In fact, I'm filled with gratitude 
to you for breaking our engagement.

251
00:18:31.660 --> 00:18:32.670
What?!

252
00:18:33.430 --> 00:18:36.010
Don't laugh at me!

253
00:18:36.010 --> 00:18:39.010
That's right! You're so mean, Lady Rishe!

254
00:18:39.010 --> 00:18:44.060
Please, don't hurt my precious Prince 
Dietrich any more than you already have!

255
00:18:44.060 --> 00:18:45.520
Lady Marie?

256
00:18:45.520 --> 00:18:49.810
Rishe, you bullied my darling 
Marie and made her cry, didn't you?

257
00:18:49.810 --> 00:18:51.400
I've heard all about it!

258
00:18:51.400 --> 00:18:56.650
Did you think that a woman as 
twisted as you could become queen?

259
00:18:58.690 --> 00:19:01.160
Please, rest at ease.

260
00:19:01.450 --> 00:19:04.510
I will obey your decree regarding 
our broken engagement.

261
00:19:04.950 --> 00:19:09.320
I will never again show 
myself before either of you.

262
00:19:09.320 --> 00:19:10.170
What?!

263
00:19:11.190 --> 00:19:15.400
Ever since I was a child, I believed that 
my position as fiancée to the crown prince

264
00:19:15.400 --> 00:19:17.530
was all that gave my life worth.

265
00:19:18.210 --> 00:19:19.930
But I was mistaken.

266
00:19:20.270 --> 00:19:22.990
I can find my worth myself.

267
00:19:22.990 --> 00:19:25.430
Now that I know that, I have all I need.

268
00:19:25.430 --> 00:19:28.020
Huh? What are you talking about?

269
00:19:31.070 --> 00:19:34.710
I do not require your presence in my life.

270
00:19:37.940 --> 00:19:39.370
Prince Dietrich!

271
00:19:39.880 --> 00:19:41.910
You're so mean, Lady Rishe!

272
00:19:41.910 --> 00:19:43.100
Lady Marie.

273
00:19:43.650 --> 00:19:48.300
Whatever lies you may tell to frame me, 
I hold no anger toward you.

274
00:19:49.270 --> 00:19:52.540
Your marriage to His Royal Highness 
is for your family's sake, isn't it?

275
00:19:52.540 --> 00:19:54.600
How do you know that?

276
00:19:55.220 --> 00:19:57.290
But please don't forget.

277
00:19:57.290 --> 00:20:01.220
If your future isn't one you wish for yourself, 
then there isn't any point to it.

278
00:20:01.500 --> 00:20:04.360
One I wish for?

279
00:20:04.890 --> 00:20:09.500
Finding happiness for your family, 
and finding happiness for yourself...

280
00:20:09.500 --> 00:20:11.230
You should be able to do both at once.

281
00:20:11.660 --> 00:20:16.860
Please lead a life where both you 
and your family can keep smiling.

282
00:20:21.630 --> 00:20:24.600
Now, the nuisance will remove herself.

283
00:20:25.280 --> 00:20:26.490
Lady Rishe!

284
00:20:26.490 --> 00:20:30.370
<i>All I have is the clothes on my back, 
just as I did in my first life.</i>

285
00:20:27.130 --> 00:20:28.440
Stop, Rishe!

286
00:20:28.440 --> 00:20:30.880
Hey, knights! Apprehend Rishe!

287
00:20:30.370 --> 00:20:33.000
<i>Now, where shall I go from here?</i>

288
00:20:30.880 --> 00:20:31.890
Sir!

289
00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:37.090
Um, Lady Rishe? If you could 
wait for just a moment...

290
00:20:47.600 --> 00:20:49.950
As I thought. It seems you're 
quite the sword master.

291
00:20:50.590 --> 00:20:54.080
Where did you learn those sword skills?

292
00:20:54.080 --> 00:20:55.900
<i>Arnold Hein.</i>

293
00:20:56.950 --> 00:20:58.360
It's a secret.

294
00:20:58.360 --> 00:21:01.510
And my skills are not so great as 
to be deserving of praise from you.

295
00:21:02.330 --> 00:21:06.340
You were holding back with 
that strike, weren't you?

296
00:21:08.160 --> 00:21:11.410
Hey, who are you? Get away from Rishe!

297
00:21:11.410 --> 00:21:13.430
Everyone, remain as you are!

298
00:21:13.430 --> 00:21:17.750
We mustn't move aggressively against 
the crown prince of Galkhein.

299
00:21:17.750 --> 00:21:20.420
The crown prince of Galkhein?!

300
00:21:20.790 --> 00:21:25.410
The beast of a prince said to have single-
handedly annihilated a troop of knights?

301
00:21:25.410 --> 00:21:28.180
Stop that! You'll be killed, too!

302
00:21:28.730 --> 00:21:32.590
Prince Arnold, may I ask 
what brings you here?

303
00:21:32.590 --> 00:21:36.260
I assume you didn't draw 
your sword just for sport.

304
00:21:36.260 --> 00:21:37.190
That's right.

305
00:21:38.340 --> 00:21:41.650
<i>My sixth life ended at the hands of this man.</i>

306
00:21:42.270 --> 00:21:45.860
<i>One day, he will cause a war 
that will envelop the whole world.</i>

307
00:21:46.490 --> 00:21:50.040
<i>The war that causes my death.</i>

308
00:21:57.130 --> 00:21:57.990
What?

309
00:21:58.840 --> 00:22:01.590
What are you doing?

310
00:22:04.050 --> 00:22:06.610
I apologize for my sudden discourtesy.

311
00:22:07.620 --> 00:22:09.350
I have something I wish to ask of you.

312
00:22:09.350 --> 00:22:10.650
Would you please...

313
00:22:12.630 --> 00:22:15.610
do me the honor of becoming my wife?

314
00:22:13.340 --> 00:22:18.340
